                            <comment id="14545636" author="stevel@apache.org" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 15:12:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;snippet of the maven dependencies with {{-Phadoop-2.4 -Dhadoop.version=2.6.0 }}&lt;/p&gt;

 &lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; [INFO] |  |  |  +- org.apache.curator:curator-client:jar:2.6.0:compile
 [INFO] |  |  |  |  +- (org.slf4j:slf4j-api:jar:1.7.10:compile - version managed from 1.7.6; omitted &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; duplicate)
 [INFO] |  |  |  |  +- (org.apache.zookeeper:zookeeper:jar:3.4.5:compile - version managed from 3.4.6; omitted &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; duplicate)
 [INFO] |  |  |  |  \- (com.google.guava:guava:jar:14.0.1:provided - version managed from 11.0.2; scope managed from compile; omitted &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; duplicate)
 [INFO] |  |  |  +- (org.apache.curator:curator-recipes:jar:2.4.0:compile - version managed from 2.6.0; omitted &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; duplicate)
 &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What&apos;s happened is that the curator-recipes version is being set by spark, but no version of curator-client is set. Nor can you fix the versions on the CLI, as the curator version isn&apos;t yet property driven.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have a patch to make things consistent, with a hadoop 2.6 profile which sets curator.version=2.6,0,  zookeeper.version=3.4.6, and drives the curator-recipes version off that curator.version property. There&apos;s one possible enhancement to this: declare the version of curator-client &amp;amp;c directly, putting the spark build in control of which version gets picked up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14545643" author="srowen" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 15:16:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah I&apos;m familiar with this flavor of problem, and it&apos;s a real pain.&lt;br/&gt;
Can we just set the version for both of these artifacts rather than make a profile, or does the curator version need to vary with Hadoop version? if the latter, yes, a new profile is OK.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14545681" author="apachespark" created="Fri, 15 May 2015 15:43:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;steveloughran&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6191&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/6191&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14547212" author="srowen" created="Sun, 17 May 2015 16:03:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 6191&lt;br/&gt;
